					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I thought the MMU registers were part of the register set.  I guess I read it wrong.<br /><br />EDIT:<br /><br />Nope, I read it correctly.  The MMU registers are separate from the logical memory space.<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">The MMU has 32 words of memory internally that describe which banks are loaded<br />into memory. The MMU memory is accessed with the MMR and MMW instructions, which<br />allow values to be read from and written into the MMU.<br /><br />The syntax for these instructions is:<br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp; MMW $00,r0&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; write the value of r0 into MMU memory word $00.<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; MMR $1F,r1&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; read the value of MMU memory word $1F into r1</div></div>

